    "headline": "What is a TFSA? Tax-Free Savings Account Explained",
    "description": "Understand how a Canadian Tax-Free Savings Account (TFSA) works, including contribution room, over-contribution penalties, and investment strategies.",
    "url": "https://westmountfundamentals.com/what-is-tfsa"
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How does a TFSA work?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "A TFSA is a registered investment account where contributions are made with after-tax dollars, but all investment growth (capital gains, dividends, and interest) and withdrawals are completely tax-free."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What happens if I over-contribute to my TFSA?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "The Canada Revenue Agency (CRA) charges a penalty tax of 1% per month on the highest excess amount in your TFSA for each month you are over your contribution limit."
        }
